WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Good morning, so our scripture reading

2
00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:04.040
is in the worship guide, if you flip it around.

3
00:00:04.040 --> 00:00:05.680
It's actually a few passages

4
00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:08.880
so that you don't have to flip between my reading.

5
00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:09.960
They're all together.

6
00:00:10.920 --> 00:00:15.920
And we're looking at when Paul was traveling to Ephesus.

7
00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:19.440
He had Priscilla and Aquila,

8
00:00:19.440 --> 00:00:23.280
you may remember those rhyming names with him.

9
00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:25.640
And so we're gonna start in Acts 18

10
00:00:25.640 --> 00:00:27.460
versus 19 through 21.

11
00:00:28.460 --> 00:00:31.700
And let's listen closely because this is God's word.

12
00:00:32.860 --> 00:00:35.260
And they came to Ephesus and he left them there,

13
00:00:35.260 --> 00:00:37.820
but he himself went into the synagogue

14
00:00:37.820 --> 00:00:39.580
and reasoned with the Jews.

15
00:00:39.580 --> 00:00:42.100
When they asked him to stay for a longer period,

16
00:00:42.100 --> 00:00:43.460
he declined.

17
00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:45.780
But on taking leave of them, he said,

18
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.500
I will return to you if God wills.

19
00:00:48.500 --> 00:00:50.500
And he set sail from Ephesus.

20
00:00:51.740 --> 00:00:55.140
And then our next passage is in chapter 19

21
00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:56.540
versus eight through 10.

22
00:00:56.540 --> 00:00:58.780
And this is when Paul returns to Ephesus

23
00:00:58.780 --> 00:01:02.180
because the Lord did will it and he did return.

24
00:01:02.180 --> 00:01:03.740
So we pick up there.

25
00:01:03.740 --> 00:01:06.700
And he entered the synagogue and for three months

26
00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:09.620
he spoke boldly reasoning and persuading them

27
00:01:09.620 --> 00:01:11.780
about the kingdom of God.

28
00:01:11.780 --> 00:01:15.540
But when some became stubborn and continued in unbelief,

29
00:01:15.540 --> 00:01:19.260
speaking evil of the way before the congregation,

30
00:01:19.260 --> 00:01:22.800
he withdrew from them and took the disciples with him,

31
00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:25.840
reasoning daily in the hall of Tyrannus.

32
00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:29.960
This continued for two years so that all the residents

33
00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:34.840
of Asia heard the word of the Lord, both Jews and Greeks.

34
00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:38.400
And then our last passage is in Ephesians one,

35
00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:39.240
one through two.

36
00:01:39.240 --> 00:01:42.280
And this is the greeting that Paul sends to those

37
00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:46.880
that he had met and known the church in Ephesus.

38
00:01:46.880 --> 00:01:51.080
Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God

39
00:01:51.080 --> 00:01:53.480
to the saints who are in Ephesus

40
00:01:53.480 --> 00:01:56.080
and are faithful in Christ Jesus.

41
00:01:56.080 --> 00:01:59.640
Grace to you and peace from God our Father

42
00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:01.760
and the Lord Jesus Christ.

43
00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:03.320
This is the word of the Lord.

44
00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:19.420
Let's pray together once again as we come to God's word.

45
00:02:20.420 --> 00:02:24.180
Lord as the rain and snow come down from heaven

46
00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:27.500
and do not return there, but what are the earth?

47
00:02:27.500 --> 00:02:30.080
Making it bring forth and sprout.

48
00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:33.500
So shall your word be that goes out from your mouth.

49
00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:36.060
It shall not return to you empty,

50
00:02:36.060 --> 00:02:38.860
but it shall accomplish that which you purpose

51
00:02:38.860 --> 00:02:42.420
and it shall succeed in the thing for which you sent it.

52
00:02:42.420 --> 00:02:44.180
So as we come now to your word,

53
00:02:44.180 --> 00:02:46.980
I pray that you would fulfill your purposes

54
00:02:46.980 --> 00:02:48.540
for your glory.

55
00:02:48.620 --> 00:02:50.940
Pray this in Jesus' name, amen.

56
00:02:53.900 --> 00:02:58.900
So do have your Bibles open there at Ephesians chapter one

57
00:02:59.180 --> 00:03:02.700
and you can refer back to those passages in Acts

58
00:03:02.700 --> 00:03:05.340
because we will look at those as well.

59
00:03:05.340 --> 00:03:06.420
But just as we get started,

60
00:03:06.420 --> 00:03:09.580
I wonder if you have any go-to movies.

61
00:03:09.580 --> 00:03:11.500
When you're not gonna watch a new one

62
00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:12.460
but you just want something

63
00:03:12.460 --> 00:03:15.140
that's an old familiar favorite,

64
00:03:15.140 --> 00:03:17.540
Julia and I, we've got sort of different genres

65
00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:21.300
that we like but we've come to the point

66
00:03:21.300 --> 00:03:23.500
of certain movies that we really agree

67
00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:27.900
that we want to watch this together for the 15th time

68
00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:29.960
and I'd say at the top on that list

69
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:32.080
is probably the Born series.

70
00:03:32.080 --> 00:03:33.740
You familiar with that?

71
00:03:33.740 --> 00:03:36.420
So the series about Jason Born.

72
00:03:36.420 --> 00:03:39.620
It begins with the movie, The Born Identity

73
00:03:39.620 --> 00:03:40.980
and it's all about this man

74
00:03:40.980 --> 00:03:44.380
who is a highly trained assassin

75
00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:46.700
but he's suffering from dementia.

76
00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:49.260
He has no idea who he is.

77
00:03:49.260 --> 00:03:51.040
He just, he wakes up

78
00:03:51.040 --> 00:03:52.700
and he's got all these skills

79
00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:55.280
from this prior training that he has

80
00:03:55.280 --> 00:03:57.760
but he's got this restlessness in him

81
00:03:57.760 --> 00:04:00.500
until he finds who he truly is.

82
00:04:00.500 --> 00:04:02.340
So the kind of point of the movie

83
00:04:02.340 --> 00:04:06.200
is this search that he has to find his true identity.

84
00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:08.880
I don't think it'd be a shock to any of us

85
00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:10.940
to say that the search for identity

86
00:04:10.940 --> 00:04:15.340
is a major theme in Western culture today

87
00:04:15.340 --> 00:04:16.780
and it's something that a lot of people

88
00:04:16.780 --> 00:04:21.020
are confused about, who they are.

89
00:04:21.020 --> 00:04:23.900
One of the main places that we have been told to look

90
00:04:23.900 --> 00:04:25.700
for years, if not decades now

91
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:29.260
is that we will find ourselves by looking within.

92
00:04:29.260 --> 00:04:31.540
It is by looking within ourselves

93
00:04:31.540 --> 00:04:35.020
that we are to find our authentic selves

94
00:04:35.020 --> 00:04:38.700
and then after we discover who we truly are,

95
00:04:38.700 --> 00:04:41.060
we're then called to, you've heard the mantra,

96
00:04:41.060 --> 00:04:43.260
be true to yourself.

97
00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:45.020
We're called to be true to ourselves.

98
00:04:45.020 --> 00:04:47.300
At least that's what our culture tells us.

99
00:04:47.300 --> 00:04:49.340
And then once you are true to yourself,

100
00:04:49.340 --> 00:04:54.340
you are to express that self to the world around you.

101
00:04:54.620 --> 00:04:56.300
And it's gotten to the point where

102
00:04:56.300 --> 00:04:59.460
how you self-identify doesn't even have to line up

103
00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:03.420
with objective reality because we've heard that so much

104
00:05:03.420 --> 00:05:05.780
that the true you is found within

105
00:05:05.780 --> 00:05:09.700
and how you identify yourself.

106
00:05:09.700 --> 00:05:12.060
Ironically, this kind of search

107
00:05:12.060 --> 00:05:15.460
for personal identity seems to be heavily influenced

108
00:05:15.460 --> 00:05:17.700
by the culture around us.

109
00:05:17.700 --> 00:05:20.020
It's supposed to be personal and by looking within

110
00:05:20.020 --> 00:05:22.300
but we look around us for our cues

111
00:05:22.300 --> 00:05:25.100
as to what the sort of thing we're supposed to find

112
00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:27.300
when we look within ourselves.

113
00:05:27.300 --> 00:05:30.100
And so that's then tied with the search

114
00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:32.500
for what group we identify with

115
00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:34.620
and what does it mean to fit in

116
00:05:34.620 --> 00:05:36.700
with the acceptable norms of that group

117
00:05:36.700 --> 00:05:38.300
that I want to be part of

118
00:05:38.300 --> 00:05:41.580
or that I feel that I am a part of.

119
00:05:41.580 --> 00:05:43.620
And so you have this restless pursuit

120
00:05:43.620 --> 00:05:45.500
that's happening in the world around us,

121
00:05:45.500 --> 00:05:47.420
particularly in Western culture today.

122
00:05:47.420 --> 00:05:52.260
And that search, needless to say, does not satisfy

123
00:05:52.260 --> 00:05:54.020
and it does not bring peace.

124
00:05:54.020 --> 00:05:58.460
It is unfulfilling and it brings about hostility

125
00:05:58.460 --> 00:06:00.300
and division between people,

126
00:06:00.300 --> 00:06:04.900
between these different group identities in society.

127
00:06:04.900 --> 00:06:06.100
But this morning I want us to see

128
00:06:06.100 --> 00:06:09.900
where true identity can be found.

129
00:06:09.900 --> 00:06:12.180
We're looking together at this introduction

130
00:06:12.180 --> 00:06:14.260
to the book of Ephesians.

131
00:06:14.260 --> 00:06:16.580
And at first glance it seems to just simply tell us

132
00:06:16.580 --> 00:06:19.580
like this is who the letter is from, it's from Paul,

133
00:06:19.580 --> 00:06:23.460
here's who the letter is to, it's to the Ephesians.

134
00:06:23.460 --> 00:06:27.740
But when you take a closer look at how they are identified

135
00:06:27.740 --> 00:06:31.180
it tells us something about our own identity

136
00:06:31.180 --> 00:06:36.180
or where we are to find our identity as followers of Jesus.

137
00:06:37.140 --> 00:06:38.260
Okay, so we'll look at that together.

138
00:06:38.260 --> 00:06:40.300
Where our identity is to be found

139
00:06:40.300 --> 00:06:43.020
and then some of the implications of that.

140
00:06:43.020 --> 00:06:47.660
So first of all, where is our identity to be found?

141
00:06:47.660 --> 00:06:51.180
Okay, so Paul's letter, it's gonna make its way to Ephesus

142
00:06:51.180 --> 00:06:53.020
and from there the letter is going to go

143
00:06:53.020 --> 00:06:54.900
throughout the whole region.

144
00:06:54.900 --> 00:06:57.900
It's written as a kind of circular letter.

145
00:06:57.900 --> 00:07:00.100
As you read through it, compared to say other letters

146
00:07:00.100 --> 00:07:01.980
like I don't know, first Corinthians,

147
00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:05.180
there's not as much personal information shared there.

148
00:07:05.220 --> 00:07:08.980
So the kind of consensus is it goes to Ephesus

149
00:07:08.980 --> 00:07:11.180
but it's not intended for Ephesus alone

150
00:07:11.180 --> 00:07:14.660
but the church at large right from the start.

151
00:07:14.660 --> 00:07:17.300
So any church can benefit from this

152
00:07:17.300 --> 00:07:19.660
and I know we can as well.

153
00:07:19.660 --> 00:07:21.700
And it makes sense that it is connected

154
00:07:21.700 --> 00:07:23.180
to the church at Ephesus.

155
00:07:23.180 --> 00:07:24.660
Like why is it listed to Ephesus here?

156
00:07:24.660 --> 00:07:26.980
Well, Ephesus was an important city

157
00:07:26.980 --> 00:07:31.100
that kind of served as a hub for the whole of Asia Minor,

158
00:07:31.100 --> 00:07:33.580
the kind of region that it was in.

159
00:07:34.460 --> 00:07:38.380
When people hear that Julia and I lived in England,

160
00:07:38.380 --> 00:07:40.380
there's certain things that come up in conversation

161
00:07:40.380 --> 00:07:42.140
almost every single time.

162
00:07:42.140 --> 00:07:45.900
And one of them is either later in the conversation,

163
00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:48.380
they just assume that we told them we are from London

164
00:07:48.380 --> 00:07:49.660
or we lived in London.

165
00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:51.340
Like as though England and London

166
00:07:51.340 --> 00:07:53.540
is just a synonym of each other.

167
00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:57.700
Or the question is how close do you live to London

168
00:07:57.700 --> 00:07:59.380
or did you live to London?

169
00:07:59.380 --> 00:08:00.780
And the reason why that is,

170
00:08:00.780 --> 00:08:02.940
it's just an obvious reference point

171
00:08:02.940 --> 00:08:05.060
that people have some familiarity with.

172
00:08:05.060 --> 00:08:08.260
And so people in conversation, polite conversation,

173
00:08:08.260 --> 00:08:09.980
they can bring up London,

174
00:08:09.980 --> 00:08:12.620
given how well known it is as a city.

175
00:08:12.620 --> 00:08:15.100
And Ephesus is that kind of city

176
00:08:15.100 --> 00:08:17.820
in that region of the Roman Empire.

177
00:08:17.820 --> 00:08:21.260
It's the third largest city at the time.

178
00:08:21.260 --> 00:08:24.500
It is a port city, so it is a kind of economic hub.

179
00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:26.340
So if you're gonna trade in Asia Minor,

180
00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:28.420
you go through Ephesus.

181
00:08:28.420 --> 00:08:30.900
Not only that, it was a religious hub.

182
00:08:30.900 --> 00:08:35.340
It was the center of the worship of Artemis specifically.

183
00:08:35.340 --> 00:08:36.860
There were some Jews there,

184
00:08:36.860 --> 00:08:41.780
but it was most known for the worship of Artemis or Diana.

185
00:08:41.780 --> 00:08:44.100
It was home to one of the wonders of the world,

186
00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:46.100
the temple of Artemis.

187
00:08:46.100 --> 00:08:48.300
And at a kind of local level,

188
00:08:48.300 --> 00:08:50.700
shrines were produced that people could purchase

189
00:08:50.700 --> 00:08:53.660
and have in their own homes.

190
00:08:53.660 --> 00:08:56.380
And so it was so tied,

191
00:08:56.380 --> 00:08:58.220
this worship of Artemis was so tied

192
00:08:58.220 --> 00:09:00.340
to the culture of Ephesus

193
00:09:00.340 --> 00:09:05.020
that Artemis was called Artemis of the Ephesians.

194
00:09:05.020 --> 00:09:08.340
People saw it as being tied to their identity.

195
00:09:08.340 --> 00:09:11.340
So to renounce your idolatry, your worship of Artemis,

196
00:09:11.340 --> 00:09:13.820
and to give allegiance to Christ and him alone

197
00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:16.620
would totally go against the grain of that culture

198
00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:18.540
and yet astonishingly,

199
00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:22.340
what we read in Acts earlier was that Ephesus became a hub

200
00:09:22.340 --> 00:09:27.220
for the advancement of the gospel through that region.

201
00:09:27.220 --> 00:09:29.660
You read that in Acts chapter 18 and 19.

202
00:09:29.660 --> 00:09:33.140
We read about how Paul and others traveled into Ephesus

203
00:09:33.140 --> 00:09:34.460
and they preached the gospel there.

204
00:09:34.460 --> 00:09:37.020
They began making disciples.

205
00:09:37.020 --> 00:09:38.540
They started off in the synagogue,

206
00:09:38.540 --> 00:09:42.100
but it wasn't long before they moved into the hall of Tyrannus.

207
00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:44.340
And from there, the gospel is just emanating

208
00:09:44.340 --> 00:09:45.580
out through the city

209
00:09:45.580 --> 00:09:48.940
and lives are being changed dramatically.

210
00:09:48.940 --> 00:09:51.220
And it emanates not only throughout the city,

211
00:09:51.220 --> 00:09:56.220
but then from the city to other areas across the region.

212
00:09:56.580 --> 00:09:58.860
And the gospel traveled so far

213
00:09:58.900 --> 00:10:01.380
that it even said in Acts chapter 19 and verse 10

214
00:10:01.380 --> 00:10:05.820
that all the residents of Asia heard the word of the Lord,

215
00:10:05.820 --> 00:10:08.420
both Jews and Greeks.

216
00:10:08.420 --> 00:10:11.580
And it doesn't seem to be that all the residents of Asia

217
00:10:11.580 --> 00:10:15.180
made a trip to Ephesus to hear the famed apostle Paul preach.

218
00:10:15.180 --> 00:10:18.180
What seems to happen in the flow when you read the passage

219
00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:20.820
is that the gospel is going out from Ephesus

220
00:10:20.820 --> 00:10:25.180
through those who heard at Ephesus to other places.

221
00:10:25.180 --> 00:10:27.100
And I'd love to get into that further,

222
00:10:27.140 --> 00:10:29.820
but just as a side note, wouldn't it be amazing

223
00:10:29.820 --> 00:10:32.860
if that is what the Lord did among us here?

224
00:10:32.860 --> 00:10:36.060
If it could be said of even just North Jefferson County,

225
00:10:36.060 --> 00:10:39.820
the word of the Lord went out to all the residents

226
00:10:39.820 --> 00:10:42.620
of North Jefferson and areas beyond.

227
00:10:44.540 --> 00:10:46.660
Well, what happened here was remarkable.

228
00:10:46.660 --> 00:10:49.500
There's no doubt about that, but it wasn't easy.

229
00:10:49.500 --> 00:10:51.940
To say that there was this amazing gospel work there,

230
00:10:51.940 --> 00:10:53.820
didn't mean that there was not opposition.

231
00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:56.260
There was opposition from the start.

232
00:10:56.300 --> 00:10:58.260
And when people's lives were changed dramatically,

233
00:10:58.260 --> 00:11:00.140
one of the hilarious things that happens

234
00:11:00.140 --> 00:11:02.580
is it begins to affect the local economy.

235
00:11:02.580 --> 00:11:05.220
So if part of the local trade was selling these shrines

236
00:11:05.220 --> 00:11:08.300
of Artemis, well, when people stopped buying those,

237
00:11:08.300 --> 00:11:10.420
well, it's gonna hurt their business.

238
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:13.020
And we even read about people who had these like magic books

239
00:11:13.020 --> 00:11:14.020
that were part of their worship,

240
00:11:14.020 --> 00:11:16.580
and they went and burnt those up as well.

241
00:11:16.580 --> 00:11:19.700
So some local craftsmen got together

242
00:11:19.700 --> 00:11:23.460
and they started stirring people up against Paul

243
00:11:23.460 --> 00:11:24.540
and his coworkers.

244
00:11:24.540 --> 00:11:27.260
And it got to the point where they got this mob together

245
00:11:27.260 --> 00:11:32.260
and they drag some of Paul's coworkers to a local stadium.

246
00:11:32.900 --> 00:11:35.420
And this mob is there in that stadium together.

247
00:11:35.420 --> 00:11:38.300
So if you watched the Alabama and Georgia game last night,

248
00:11:38.300 --> 00:11:40.500
you got some idea of what we're talking about here,

249
00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:43.420
minus some of the lights and all the rest.

250
00:11:44.940 --> 00:11:46.760
So you got this stadium, but what are people chanting?

251
00:11:46.760 --> 00:11:48.820
It's not Roll Tide or anything else.

252
00:11:48.820 --> 00:11:52.820
They are chanting, great is Artemis of the Ephesians,

253
00:11:52.860 --> 00:11:56.860
over and over in its roaring and the cultures speaking together

254
00:11:56.860 --> 00:12:00.180
in one voice and to say anything different

255
00:12:00.180 --> 00:12:03.400
would have been really, really hard.

256
00:12:03.400 --> 00:12:06.180
So where is identity to be found?

257
00:12:06.180 --> 00:12:09.340
Well, it's not to be found in Ephesus.

258
00:12:09.340 --> 00:12:11.740
The pressure to conform to culture there

259
00:12:11.740 --> 00:12:13.380
was literally deafening.

260
00:12:13.380 --> 00:12:17.700
And I would say that that is true in our day as well.

261
00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:19.500
Is that not the case?

262
00:12:19.500 --> 00:12:20.860
There's a pressure to conform.

263
00:12:20.860 --> 00:12:22.980
We are surrounded by cultural currents

264
00:12:22.980 --> 00:12:25.580
that will pull us away from Christ

265
00:12:25.580 --> 00:12:28.500
if we are not intentionally following Him

266
00:12:28.500 --> 00:12:30.060
in the opposite direction.

267
00:12:30.060 --> 00:12:33.220
And if you don't feel the pull of those currents

268
00:12:33.220 --> 00:12:35.860
and may just be that you are drifting

269
00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:38.980
with the culture around you.

270
00:12:38.980 --> 00:12:41.580
Now this can be confusing in America

271
00:12:41.580 --> 00:12:44.780
and maybe Alabama specifically or the Bible Belt

272
00:12:44.780 --> 00:12:48.060
because Christianity and culture can be so mixed together.

273
00:12:48.100 --> 00:12:52.100
It's hard to pick out which one is which.

274
00:12:52.100 --> 00:12:53.940
In Ephesus it might have looked like,

275
00:12:53.940 --> 00:12:55.220
I don't know if you sort of mixed the two,

276
00:12:55.220 --> 00:12:57.220
having a crucifix up in one room

277
00:12:57.220 --> 00:13:00.700
and then I don't know a shrine to Artemis in the next,

278
00:13:00.700 --> 00:13:03.820
thinking you could sort of play it both ways.

279
00:13:03.820 --> 00:13:05.820
In Alabama it might look like,

280
00:13:05.820 --> 00:13:09.100
I don't know believing that Jesus will save your soul

281
00:13:09.100 --> 00:13:11.300
but He really doesn't care about what you do

282
00:13:11.300 --> 00:13:13.100
with your body because you're just supposed

283
00:13:13.100 --> 00:13:15.140
to be true to yourself, right?

284
00:13:15.140 --> 00:13:16.340
See here those two,

285
00:13:16.340 --> 00:13:17.660
the cultural current pulling you

286
00:13:17.660 --> 00:13:20.380
while at the same time wanting to have a bit of Jesus

287
00:13:20.380 --> 00:13:22.740
in there too.

288
00:13:22.740 --> 00:13:24.540
And by the way, this isn't a right thing

289
00:13:24.540 --> 00:13:26.500
or a left thing either.

290
00:13:27.500 --> 00:13:31.820
This can be found on all sides of the political aisle

291
00:13:31.820 --> 00:13:33.780
or the sort of the cultural things

292
00:13:33.780 --> 00:13:36.940
that get tied up into those two categories.

293
00:13:36.940 --> 00:13:41.560
So we cannot look to our culture for our identity.

294
00:13:41.560 --> 00:13:42.620
So where do we look?

295
00:13:42.620 --> 00:13:43.620
Where can it be found?

296
00:13:43.620 --> 00:13:45.580
Well it is found in Christ.

297
00:13:45.580 --> 00:13:48.980
So yes, so these believers are in Ephesus, verse one,

298
00:13:48.980 --> 00:13:50.340
but they are also faithful.

299
00:13:50.340 --> 00:13:55.340
Notice these words in Christ, Jesus.

300
00:13:55.500 --> 00:13:58.920
And those two words in Christ or in Christ Jesus

301
00:13:58.920 --> 00:14:00.460
are incredibly important.

302
00:14:00.460 --> 00:14:02.700
This is a major theme that stretches right the way

303
00:14:02.700 --> 00:14:04.100
throughout the New Testament,

304
00:14:04.100 --> 00:14:05.660
especially in Paul's letters

305
00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:06.700
and within Paul's letters,

306
00:14:06.700 --> 00:14:08.380
especially the book of Ephesians.

307
00:14:08.380 --> 00:14:11.460
We're gonna see this over and over throughout the book.

308
00:14:11.460 --> 00:14:14.780
So we need to hear what the Lord is saying

309
00:14:14.820 --> 00:14:17.740
by telling us about what it means to be in Christ.

310
00:14:17.740 --> 00:14:20.980
And the doctrine that these two words point us to

311
00:14:20.980 --> 00:14:23.500
being in Christ is traditionally referred to

312
00:14:23.500 --> 00:14:25.820
as our union with Christ.

313
00:14:25.820 --> 00:14:27.220
It's kind of in recent years

314
00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:28.360
that people have started talking more

315
00:14:28.360 --> 00:14:30.740
about our identity in Christ,

316
00:14:30.740 --> 00:14:33.300
perhaps in response to what we're hearing in our culture.

317
00:14:33.300 --> 00:14:34.380
But traditionally we've thought

318
00:14:34.380 --> 00:14:38.020
about our union with Christ.

319
00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:38.860
So what does that mean?

320
00:14:38.860 --> 00:14:41.460
What is union with Christ?

321
00:14:41.460 --> 00:14:42.860
It can be tricky to define,

322
00:14:42.860 --> 00:14:44.620
I'll just say that from the start.

323
00:14:44.980 --> 00:14:47.220
It's been described along these lines.

324
00:14:47.220 --> 00:14:48.780
So listen carefully.

325
00:14:48.780 --> 00:14:53.780
It is a close living spiritual union

326
00:14:55.100 --> 00:14:58.220
between Christ and his people.

327
00:14:58.220 --> 00:15:01.740
And from this union flows life,

328
00:15:01.740 --> 00:15:05.060
blessing and salvation.

329
00:15:05.060 --> 00:15:05.900
I'll say it again.

330
00:15:05.900 --> 00:15:08.420
It's a close living spiritual union

331
00:15:08.420 --> 00:15:10.140
between Christ and his people.

332
00:15:10.140 --> 00:15:12.460
And from this union with him

333
00:15:12.500 --> 00:15:17.140
flows our life, blessings and salvation.

334
00:15:17.140 --> 00:15:18.340
Or to put more simply,

335
00:15:18.340 --> 00:15:21.740
to be united to Christ is to have your life

336
00:15:21.740 --> 00:15:26.300
bound up with his and to receive all the good

337
00:15:26.300 --> 00:15:28.140
that flows from that.

338
00:15:28.140 --> 00:15:30.300
It's to have died with him

339
00:15:30.300 --> 00:15:32.460
and to be risen with him.

340
00:15:32.460 --> 00:15:34.740
To have your life bound to his.

341
00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:36.660
And several metaphors are used in scripture

342
00:15:36.660 --> 00:15:39.060
and maybe these pictures help us to understand better

343
00:15:39.060 --> 00:15:40.780
than kind of trying to define it.

344
00:15:40.780 --> 00:15:43.020
One is Jesus in John 15.

345
00:15:43.020 --> 00:15:46.340
I am divine, you are the branches, right?

346
00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:47.660
That's a living relationship

347
00:15:47.660 --> 00:15:49.380
between the Lord and his people.

348
00:15:49.380 --> 00:15:51.380
Colossians chapter one and verse 18

349
00:15:51.380 --> 00:15:52.940
as other places in scripture.

350
00:15:52.940 --> 00:15:55.260
He is the body of the church,

351
00:15:55.260 --> 00:15:56.980
or no, sorry, he is the head of the church

352
00:15:56.980 --> 00:15:58.300
and we are the body of the church, right?

353
00:15:58.300 --> 00:15:59.900
So there's a living relationship

354
00:15:59.900 --> 00:16:02.740
between the head and the body.

355
00:16:02.740 --> 00:16:05.380
Here in Ephesians, in Ephesians chapter five,

356
00:16:05.380 --> 00:16:08.420
you see the marital union of a husband and wife

357
00:16:08.420 --> 00:16:10.100
when two become one,

358
00:16:10.300 --> 00:16:11.980
that is there as a picture of Christ

359
00:16:11.980 --> 00:16:15.140
and his church of our union with him.

360
00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:17.100
So who we are, in other words,

361
00:16:17.100 --> 00:16:20.820
is vitally connected to who he is

362
00:16:20.820 --> 00:16:22.660
if we are in Christ.

363
00:16:22.660 --> 00:16:24.820
And that is distinct from our old selves,

364
00:16:24.820 --> 00:16:26.300
our previous identity.

365
00:16:26.300 --> 00:16:29.940
Our old self died with Christ.

366
00:16:29.940 --> 00:16:33.380
And then we are united to him

367
00:16:33.380 --> 00:16:35.740
and in that union we now have new life in him.

368
00:16:35.740 --> 00:16:37.500
Paul said it this way in Galatians chapter two

369
00:16:37.540 --> 00:16:41.060
and verse 20, I am, this is who I am,

370
00:16:41.060 --> 00:16:42.860
crucified with Christ.

371
00:16:42.860 --> 00:16:44.820
Nevertheless, I live yet not I,

372
00:16:44.820 --> 00:16:47.220
but Christ lives in me.

373
00:16:48.980 --> 00:16:50.780
This isn't just true of our relationship

374
00:16:50.780 --> 00:16:54.700
with Christ personally, but also collectively.

375
00:16:55.580 --> 00:16:58.220
So this isn't just a letter to an individual,

376
00:16:58.220 --> 00:17:00.640
this is a letter to the church.

377
00:17:00.640 --> 00:17:03.860
So our union with Jesus brings about communion

378
00:17:03.860 --> 00:17:05.700
with one another, right?

379
00:17:05.700 --> 00:17:08.220
We're brought into this body.

380
00:17:08.220 --> 00:17:09.540
If you are in Jesus,

381
00:17:09.540 --> 00:17:11.900
you are part of a new community

382
00:17:11.900 --> 00:17:14.540
that he is creating called the church.

383
00:17:16.180 --> 00:17:17.860
So this book shows us what it means

384
00:17:17.860 --> 00:17:20.320
to be part of his church, his body.

385
00:17:21.780 --> 00:17:24.100
So our identity is not to be found in the world,

386
00:17:24.100 --> 00:17:25.940
but in Christ.

387
00:17:25.940 --> 00:17:27.340
But secondly, I want us to see this.

388
00:17:27.340 --> 00:17:30.100
So if it's to be found in Christ,

389
00:17:30.100 --> 00:17:31.140
we then have to ask the question,

390
00:17:31.140 --> 00:17:33.460
well, who are we in Christ then?

391
00:17:33.620 --> 00:17:35.700
I'm still not sure who it is, we are.

392
00:17:36.820 --> 00:17:38.620
So I'll draw our attention to a couple of things

393
00:17:38.620 --> 00:17:41.660
about our identity that are true of us in Jesus.

394
00:17:41.660 --> 00:17:44.900
So first of all, in Christ, we are saints.

395
00:17:44.900 --> 00:17:46.260
So did you see that?

396
00:17:46.260 --> 00:17:49.420
In verse one, Paul is writing to the saints.

397
00:17:51.300 --> 00:17:52.700
So what does it mean?

398
00:17:52.700 --> 00:17:56.980
Well, the word means set apart, consecrated, holy.

399
00:17:58.620 --> 00:18:00.820
It's what we saw kind of about the world a minute ago

400
00:18:00.820 --> 00:18:02.900
that we've been separated from the world.

401
00:18:02.940 --> 00:18:05.460
So saints are in the world, but no longer of it,

402
00:18:05.460 --> 00:18:08.140
we are set apart.

403
00:18:08.140 --> 00:18:10.500
But who can this really be said of saints?

404
00:18:10.500 --> 00:18:13.700
Like saints is another one of those confusing words

405
00:18:13.700 --> 00:18:15.140
that's kind of thrown around sometimes

406
00:18:15.140 --> 00:18:17.060
and it always never means what it actually means

407
00:18:17.060 --> 00:18:17.900
in scripture.

408
00:18:17.900 --> 00:18:20.060
So we might think of saints as being,

409
00:18:20.060 --> 00:18:22.420
I don't know, that heroes of church history

410
00:18:22.420 --> 00:18:26.940
who are in heaven, ready to help us in our time of needs.

411
00:18:26.940 --> 00:18:29.420
Maybe you grew up thinking or hearing of saints

412
00:18:29.420 --> 00:18:30.820
in that way.

413
00:18:30.820 --> 00:18:31.860
There's some who believe,

414
00:18:31.900 --> 00:18:34.420
there's a kind of saint for every occasion

415
00:18:34.420 --> 00:18:37.500
and I've gone online to see just how many different

416
00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:39.340
specializations saints have.

417
00:18:39.340 --> 00:18:42.700
And I stopped once I got halfway through the bees, right?

418
00:18:42.700 --> 00:18:46.940
Cause there was literally a saint for bees.

419
00:18:46.940 --> 00:18:48.540
There was a saint for bookkeeping.

420
00:18:48.540 --> 00:18:50.620
There was a saint for bridges and the list

421
00:18:50.620 --> 00:18:51.940
went on and on and on.

422
00:18:51.940 --> 00:18:53.920
That's not what we have here.

423
00:18:55.180 --> 00:18:57.260
It's also used to describe somebody who's just

424
00:18:57.260 --> 00:19:00.820
patiently puts up with a lot.

425
00:19:00.820 --> 00:19:05.180
I don't know how in the world she deals with those children.

426
00:19:05.180 --> 00:19:07.300
She really is a saint.

427
00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:09.860
I know I use it from time to time.

428
00:19:10.980 --> 00:19:13.540
But biblically speaking, the category of saint

429
00:19:13.540 --> 00:19:18.380
is not a kind of, it's not the VIP section of Christians.

430
00:19:18.380 --> 00:19:22.460
It is a term that is applied to every Christian.

431
00:19:22.460 --> 00:19:25.220
If you are in Christ, you are a saint.

432
00:19:26.380 --> 00:19:29.780
You might think, well, if you knew some of the things

433
00:19:29.820 --> 00:19:33.980
that I've done in my life, you would not call me a saint.

434
00:19:35.100 --> 00:19:39.580
But let me repeat, if you are in Christ,

435
00:19:39.580 --> 00:19:43.180
that is exactly who you are.

436
00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:46.060
I'm gonna take that a step further.

437
00:19:47.620 --> 00:19:50.120
Around 40 times in the New Testament,

438
00:19:50.120 --> 00:19:52.740
Paul refers to Christians as saints

439
00:19:52.740 --> 00:19:55.420
as those who've been made holy.

440
00:19:56.420 --> 00:19:59.020
How many times does Paul refer to Christians

441
00:19:59.060 --> 00:20:01.740
to those who are in Christ as sinners?

442
00:20:02.900 --> 00:20:07.900
The answer is zero, not one time.

443
00:20:08.900 --> 00:20:11.540
Now to be fair, there is one time in the New Testament

444
00:20:11.540 --> 00:20:14.380
where James refers to backsliding Christians

445
00:20:14.380 --> 00:20:16.340
who were living as though they were not believers

446
00:20:16.340 --> 00:20:19.260
as sinners descriptively, like they are sinning,

447
00:20:19.260 --> 00:20:21.100
so they're sinners, like so, if you say that,

448
00:20:21.100 --> 00:20:23.940
don't feel bad that you've said that at some point.

449
00:20:23.940 --> 00:20:28.940
But nonetheless, it's not talking about their identity.

450
00:20:29.060 --> 00:20:31.380
If you are in Christ, it is true to say

451
00:20:31.380 --> 00:20:33.980
that you were a sinner.

452
00:20:33.980 --> 00:20:35.540
That's true of all of us.

453
00:20:35.540 --> 00:20:38.860
You were a sinner, for sure, me too.

454
00:20:38.860 --> 00:20:40.820
It's true to say that even in Christ,

455
00:20:40.820 --> 00:20:43.260
even as a Christian, you still struggle with sin

456
00:20:43.260 --> 00:20:46.300
on a daily basis, yes, but hear me,

457
00:20:46.300 --> 00:20:50.220
that is no longer your identity.

458
00:20:50.220 --> 00:20:54.060
If you are in Christ, you have categorically been moved

459
00:20:54.060 --> 00:20:56.980
from sinner to saint.

460
00:20:59.220 --> 00:21:02.420
That is your God-given identity.

461
00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:06.180
And the Christian life is simply learning to live

462
00:21:06.180 --> 00:21:09.660
in light of that new identity that has been given us

463
00:21:09.660 --> 00:21:12.500
in Jesus, and that's that kind of faithfulness

464
00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:14.420
that we see there in verse one when they are,

465
00:21:14.420 --> 00:21:16.460
they're faithful in Christ Jesus.

466
00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:18.100
They've been set apart, and that's coming through

467
00:21:18.100 --> 00:21:20.300
in the way they're living now.

468
00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:23.260
Here's the deal, in Jesus' death,

469
00:21:23.260 --> 00:21:25.740
he's already done everything to completely

470
00:21:25.740 --> 00:21:28.380
cleanse his people from their sin.

471
00:21:28.420 --> 00:21:32.980
So the question is, are you in him, or are you not?

472
00:21:32.980 --> 00:21:36.460
If you're in Christ, you're no longer defined by your sin,

473
00:21:36.460 --> 00:21:37.660
but by your savior.

474
00:21:37.660 --> 00:21:41.260
In other words, in him, you're a saint.

475
00:21:42.740 --> 00:21:44.820
But also, who else are we in him?

476
00:21:44.820 --> 00:21:47.380
We are children of God.

477
00:21:47.380 --> 00:21:48.940
So notice what he says in verse two,

478
00:21:48.940 --> 00:21:53.380
grace to you and peace from God our Father

479
00:21:53.380 --> 00:21:55.580
and the Lord Jesus Christ.

480
00:21:55.580 --> 00:21:57.860
Mark those two words, our Father.

481
00:21:58.380 --> 00:22:01.780
If you're in Christ, you can say he is my Father.

482
00:22:02.900 --> 00:22:05.340
God is my heavenly Father.

483
00:22:05.340 --> 00:22:08.060
It isn't a controversial statement to say

484
00:22:08.060 --> 00:22:13.060
that our families of origin profoundly shape our lives.

485
00:22:15.100 --> 00:22:17.220
It impacts the way we view ourselves,

486
00:22:17.220 --> 00:22:20.940
it impacts the way we interact with the world around us,

487
00:22:20.940 --> 00:22:24.580
and that's true positively, but I'd imagine

488
00:22:24.580 --> 00:22:26.620
our minds didn't first go to the positives,

489
00:22:26.620 --> 00:22:29.740
or at least for many of us, it can impact us negatively

490
00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:32.540
as well, and for all of us it's probably a bit of both.

491
00:22:33.860 --> 00:22:36.060
It's an incredibly complex thing,

492
00:22:36.060 --> 00:22:37.780
and it varies from family to family,

493
00:22:37.780 --> 00:22:39.020
and person to person.

494
00:22:39.980 --> 00:22:43.420
But here's this, if you are in Christ,

495
00:22:43.420 --> 00:22:48.420
you are no longer defined by your family of origin.

496
00:22:48.620 --> 00:22:51.580
You're no longer defined by your background.

497
00:22:51.580 --> 00:22:56.580
You are first and foremost a child of God.

498
00:22:56.620 --> 00:23:00.060
However, you are treated by earthly parents,

499
00:23:00.060 --> 00:23:02.620
whatever you were told.

500
00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:05.420
If you are in Christ, you have a heavenly Father

501
00:23:05.420 --> 00:23:08.180
who loves you more than you could possibly know

502
00:23:08.180 --> 00:23:11.280
and will care for you and provide all that you need.

503
00:23:11.280 --> 00:23:16.280
His home is a home of grace and peace.

504
00:23:18.660 --> 00:23:21.540
So, however you feel in Christ,

505
00:23:21.540 --> 00:23:23.700
you can know that you belong to your heavenly Father.

506
00:23:23.700 --> 00:23:25.020
So who are we?

507
00:23:25.020 --> 00:23:25.860
Who are you?

508
00:23:27.060 --> 00:23:29.260
If your faith is in Christ, if you're united to Him,

509
00:23:29.260 --> 00:23:33.520
you are His, you belong to Him as a saint, as a child of God.

510
00:23:35.060 --> 00:23:37.260
But lastly, how does that come about?

511
00:23:37.260 --> 00:23:39.700
We find this identity in Christ, we see that we're saints

512
00:23:39.700 --> 00:23:41.140
and we're children of God,

513
00:23:41.140 --> 00:23:44.540
but how is that brought about in our lives?

514
00:23:44.540 --> 00:23:46.980
How did it happen in Ephesus?

515
00:23:46.980 --> 00:23:49.580
Well, there's lots that could be said here,

516
00:23:49.580 --> 00:23:52.700
but I wanna focus on a couple of things.

517
00:23:52.700 --> 00:23:55.380
I want us to see that God brings this about

518
00:23:55.420 --> 00:23:58.280
by His word and by His will.

519
00:23:59.500 --> 00:24:02.460
So Paul was involved in their conversion

520
00:24:02.460 --> 00:24:04.880
and in their ongoing growth in Christ,

521
00:24:04.880 --> 00:24:06.780
but he doesn't take credit for it here.

522
00:24:06.780 --> 00:24:08.540
He makes it clear that God is the one

523
00:24:08.540 --> 00:24:09.380
who's brought this about.

524
00:24:09.380 --> 00:24:12.380
He was the human instrument, but this is the Lord's work

525
00:24:12.380 --> 00:24:15.420
and he worked through His word and through His will.

526
00:24:16.300 --> 00:24:17.380
So where do we see that?

527
