the wine is non-alcoholic

790
00:36:06.540 --> 00:36:08.860
and over to my left, to your right,

791
00:36:08.900 --> 00:36:12.500
there's a gluten-free option there if that is needed.

792
00:36:13.740 --> 00:36:15.460
But if you're trusting in Christ

793
00:36:15.460 --> 00:36:17.820
for the forgiveness of your sins

794
00:36:17.820 --> 00:36:20.740
and you have publicly identified with him in baptism,

795
00:36:20.740 --> 00:36:24.260
then I'd invite you to partake with us

796
00:36:24.260 --> 00:36:28.700
in this meal together, remembering Jesus' death for us.

797
00:36:29.780 --> 00:36:32.940
But if that's not you, if you're not sure

798
00:36:32.940 --> 00:36:35.380
whether or not you are in Christ,

799
00:36:35.380 --> 00:36:36.940
whether or not you're following him,

800
00:36:36.940 --> 00:36:41.660
I would ask you to refrain from taking this,

801
00:36:41.660 --> 00:36:44.300
but to at the same time ponder

802
00:36:44.300 --> 00:36:46.540
and prayerfully consider the message

803
00:36:46.540 --> 00:36:48.020
that is being proclaimed through it,

804
00:36:48.020 --> 00:36:50.300
Jesus' death for us.

805
00:36:50.300 --> 00:36:53.940
And hear the invitation to come to him by faith.

806
00:36:53.940 --> 00:36:56.460
So as we take this time to remember Jesus' death,

807
00:36:56.460 --> 00:36:59.300
let's pause and take a moment to pray

808
00:36:59.300 --> 00:37:00.860
before we come to this table.

809
00:37:36.940 --> 00:37:38.820
I'm going to be now praising your great name

810
00:37:38.820 --> 00:37:41.180
for all that you have done for us in Christ.

811
00:37:42.700 --> 00:37:43.780
As we come to your table,

812
00:37:43.780 --> 00:37:45.260
we want to especially thank you

813
00:37:45.260 --> 00:37:48.580
for his sacrificial and substitutionary death

814
00:37:48.580 --> 00:37:50.100
for us on the cross.

815
00:37:51.140 --> 00:37:54.820
He took our sin that we might be made saints.

816
00:37:54.820 --> 00:37:58.380
He was forsaken that we might be welcomed as family.

817
00:37:59.380 --> 00:38:02.140
So as we partake in this bread and wine,

818
00:38:02.140 --> 00:38:05.020
help us to receive it by faith

819
00:38:05.140 --> 00:38:07.820
and with thanksgiving in Jesus' name.

820
00:38:08.820 --> 00:38:09.660
Amen.

